8 An Act relating to public lands; amending Section 1,
Chapter 175, O.S.L. 2024 (64 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
9 1097), which relates to unauthorized camps;
prohibiting use of county- or municipal-owned lands
10 for unauthorized camps; authorizing counties and
municipalities to opt out of prohibition; and
11 providing an effective date.
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 175, O.S.L.
15 2024 (64 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 1097), is amended to read as
16 follows:
17 Section 1097. A. As used in this section, "unauthorized camp"
18 means any tent, shelter, or bedding constructed or arranged for the
19 purpose of or in such a way to permit overnight use on a property
20 not designated as a campsite.
21 B. Persons may not use state-owned, county-owned, or municipal-
22 owned lands for the purposes of establishing an unauthorized camp.
23 C. Any person who violates the provisions of this section
24 shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a
