1 fine not to exceed Fifty Dollars ($50.00) or by imprisonment in the
2 county jail not to exceed fifteen (15) days, or by both such fine
3 and imprisonment. However, a person who commits a first violation
4 of this section shall be issued a warning, and a citation may not be
5 issued unless the person refuses any assistance offered to them by
6 the arresting officer. Such assistance may include, but is not
7 limited to, transportation to a shelter, food pantry, or other place
8 where resources are made available to assist the indigent and
9 homeless.
10 D. The governing body of any county or municipality may opt out
11 of this section by a majority vote of the governing body.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
